entries.title: 'It is a political game': Nephew speaks of anguish at execution of British-Iranian national
entries.description: The nephew of a British-Iranian national who was put to death by hanging in Iran has spoken of his shock, describing the execution as a "political game".

entries.title: Luxury cars seized from influencer Andrew Tate's villa in Romania
entries.description: Romanian authorities have seized several luxury cars from influencer Andrew Tate's villa as part of a criminal inquiry into alleged human trafficking that led to his arrest.

entries.title: Lithuania gas pipeline explosion 'likely caused by technical malfunction'
entries.description: A powerful gas pipeline explosion which sent flames 150ft into the sky in northern Lithuania was most likely caused by a technical malfunction, officials have said.

entries.title: Thousands protest against controversial coal mine in Germany
entries.description: Around 6,000 demonstrators, including Swedish climate change activist Greta Thunberg, have gathered in western Germany to protest the clearance of a village to make way for the expansion of a controversial coal mine.

entries.title: Britain to send Challenger 2 tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Britain is to send Challenger 2 tanks to Ukraine to bolster the war effort against invading Russian forces.

entries.title: China reports almost 60,000 COVID-related deaths in just over a month
entries.description: China has reported almost 60,000 COVID-related deaths since early December.

entries.title: Jailed Putin critic Alexei Navalny 'needs urgent medical assistance'
entries.description: Germany has called on Russia to provide "urgent medical assistance" to jailed opposition politician Alexei Navalny.

entries.title: $1.35bn lottery jackpot won by single ticketholder in US
entries.description: A single ticketholder has won an estimated $1.35bn dollars (£1.1bn) in the US Mega Millions lottery.

entries.title: 'Tortured, drugged and forced to confess': Who was the British-Iranian national executed in Iran?
entries.description: Iran has executed a British-Iranian national after accusing him of spying for the UK.

entries.title: World's longest working DJ whose Beatles interview made him a celebrity dies
entries.description: The world's longest working DJ who spun the wheels of steel over six decades has died aged 98.

entries.title: British-Iranian national Alireza Akbari 'executed' in Iran - report
entries.description: British-Iranian national Alireza Akbari, a former senior defence official in Iran accused of working for British intelligence, has been executed, according to Iran's state media.

entries.title: Bolsonaro to be investigated for allegedly inciting riots at Brazil's government buildings
entries.description: Brazil's former president Jair Bolsonaro is to be investigated for allegedly encouraging protests that ended with his supporters storming several government buildings.

entries.title: 'It's great to be back': Djokovic gets warm welcome in first match in Melbourne since being deported and banned
entries.description: Novak Djokovic has received a warm welcome on his first return to Melbourne since being held in custody and banned from entering Australia due to his vaccination status.
